    <caption>
      <p> Pre-calculated or live CD-Search results are readily available for protein sequences in Entrez. Clicking on the colored bars will launch alignment displays that merge the query into the domain alignment model, for further analysis. Domain annotation bars with identical colors have been grouped into sets of ‘related’ domains, indicating that they share many of the sequence intervals hit with significant <italic>E</italic>-values. Annotation bars colored in gray have been classified as putative multi-domain models and are excluded from domain–domain neighboring. The lower half of the figure displays a graphical representation of a domain family hierarchy, giving the summary for one particular member (cd01366).</p>
    </caption>
